Three men have died in a devastating one-car-crash in the seaside town of Eastbourne. The men, aged 32, 36 and 21, were from Berkshire and were pronounced dead at the scene after 11.10pm last night. It is not yet clear exactly what happened, but pictures today showed the vehicle extensively damaged. The seaside town saw heavy fog last night, including around the time the accident happened. Police say the crash, on Decoy Drive in Eastbourne, involved the one car. The menâ€™s families have been informed about the tragedy. Officers are appealing for anyone who witnessed the event, or any details leading up to it, to come forward. Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.